Commands for managing MCPAccessGrant and MCPAgentSession resources that feed the gateway policy layer.

With mcp-runtime auth login, commands use the platform API by default for normal
user and admin workflows. Use --use-kube only for admin/dev/test direct
Kubernetes operations; it requires kubectl plus admin/operator kubeconfig and
RBAC access. For platform workflows, run mcp-runtime auth login --api-url
<platform-url> and stay on the platform API path.

Usage:
  mcp-runtime access [command]

Available Commands:
  grant       Manage MCPAccessGrant resources
  session     Manage MCPAgentSession resources

Flags:
  -h, --help       help for access
      --use-kube   Use direct Kubernetes mode with kubectl; requires admin/operator cluster access (admin/dev/test only)

Global Flags:
      --debug   Enable debug mode with structured error logging

Use "mcp-runtime access [command] --help" for more information about a command.
